TY  - JOUR
T1  - Research Productivity of Graduates in Management: Effects of Academic Origin and Academic Affiliation
AU  - Long, Rebecca G.
AU  - Bowers, William P.
AU  - Barnett, Tim
AU  - White, Michael C.
Y1  - 1998/12/01
PY  - 1998
DA  - 1998/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256966
DO  - 10.5465/256966
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 704
EP  - 714
VL  - 41
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We examined the relationships among status of academic origin, status of academic affiliation, and research productivity for a sample of doctoral graduates in management. Contrary to expectations, the status of a graduate's academic origin did not appear to be strongly associated with his or her research productivity. The status of his or her academic affiliation, however, had a relatively strong association with research productivity in terms of both number of publications in top journals and citation counts of these publications.
AB  - We examined the relationships among status of academic origin, status of academic affiliation, and research productivity for a sample of doctoral graduates in management. Contrary to expectations, the status of a graduate's academic origin did not appear to be strongly associated with his or her research productivity. The status of his or her academic affiliation, however, had a relatively strong association with research productivity in terms of both number of publications in top journals and citation counts of these publications.
